 :tx/rationale "DESIGN INSIGHT: JOIN_THRESHOLD and similar constants should be learnable datoms, not hard-coded constants. The threshold 0.20 was found empirically but is model-specific and possibly domain-specific. The right architecture: (1) Store the threshold as a policy datom :policy/concept-join-threshold with a default. (2) The hypothesis ledger can test whether a threshold change improves concept assignment quality. (3) The calibration loop (OBSERVER-4) adjusts the threshold based on predicted vs actual outcomes. (4) Different projects may discover different optimal thresholds. (5) Thresholds are CRDT-mergeable via set union — two teams that independently calibrate can share their learning. This is the self-tuning feedback loop: observe → assign → validate → adjust threshold → better assignments. The system finds its own optimum empirically. Other candidates for learnable parameters: SPLIT_THRESHOLD (0.5), MERGE_THRESHOLD (0.85), MIN_CLUSTER_SIZE (3), DEFAULT_ALPHA (2.0). All should be policy datoms with sensible defaults."
